news.title: Incuspaze appoints Mayank Kaushik as COO and Kapil Poddar as CFO
news.para: Sanjay Choudhary, founder and CEO of Incuspaze said, "As we expand our footprint across India, fortifying our leadership team is essential to achieving operational excellence and strategic clarity."

news.title: Jaideep Ahlawat along with wife buys apartment in Mumbai for ₹10 crore
news.para: The purchased apartment features a carpet area of 1,950 sq ft (181 sq meter) and a built-up area of 2,341 sq ft (217.47 sq meter), according to the Inspector General of Registration (IGR) documents reviewed by Square Yards.

news.title: Mumbai: Kurla dairy land will be used for ineligible Dharavi residents’ rehabilitation
news.para: ​In a press release, the govt said 8.5 lakh people are to be rehabilitated under the project, of whom five lakh will be rehabilitated in Dharavi and 3.5 lakh outside the Dharavi Notified Area (DNA).

news.title: Haridwar locals struggle to sell properties near waste site where civic body bought land at inflated rate
news.para: Villagers were shocked to learn that the Haridwar Nagar Nigam purchased the land for Rs 54 crore, even as they themselves struggle to sell their properties, despite slashing prices, due to the foul odour and polluted air from the dumping site.

news.title: Sambalpur civic body partners with SPA for urban development
news.para: The MoU signed under the guidance of Union education minister Dharmendra Pradhan aims to leverage SPA Delhi's expertise in transforming Sambalpur into a model city.

news.title: Houses outside lal dora in Chandigarh to get water connections but at a hefty price
news.para: ​According to the opposition, water connections should be provided without imposing double domestic charges and construction charges on old buildings. Regardless of their protests, the mayor and BJP councillors approved the agenda.

news.title: Pay your holding tax by June 30, avail up to 10% rebate: Ranchi civic body
news.para: "The RMC has collected Rs 22 crore in holding tax payments for the financial year 2025–26, achieving 23% of its annual target of Rs 97 crore," deputy municipal commissioner Gautam Prasad Sahu said.

news.title: About 300 revenue officers in Odisha issued show-cause notices for land sale norms flout
news.para: "Officers who were on DSR duty between 2014 and 2024 and indulged in illegal activities are facing disciplinary proceedings. Some of them even faced criminal charges and are in jail," revenue minister Suresh Pujari said.

news.title: DDA seeks to make parking allocation in housing projects fair
news.para: According to DDA, the policy considers the specific requirements of different flat categories and the needs of persons with disabilities (PwD) as well as cases requiring special attention on genuine medical grounds.

news.title: Lucknow buildings high & dry, bereft of rainwater harvesting benefits
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority includes rainwater harvesting provisions while approving building plans. The ground reality, however, paints a different picture.

news.title: Karnataka pollution control board tightens rules for high-rise projects
news.para: If these clearances are not obtained and the Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) still issues CC and OC, the responsibility will rest entirely with the BBMP.

news.title: WeWork leases over 60,000 sq ft of managed office space to Samsung India Electronics
news.para: Samsung India has expanded its Chennai operations. The company leased 1,000 desks at WeWork's Olympia Cyberspace. The 42-month lease covers 61,230 square feet. This doubles Samsung's Chennai footprint. The move highlights Chennai's rise as a tech hub.

news.title: Pune: Housing for displaced families remains on paper as action against illegal structures begins
news.para: PMRDA, with jurisdiction over 6,000 square km consisting of around 3,500 identified illegal structures, has yet to operationalise the mechanism.

news.title: State will be first to reach 100% target of PMAY scheme: Maharashtra CM
news.para: The CM was speaking at a PM Awas Yojana award function in Pune with Union minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan as the chief guest. Deputy CM Ajit Pawar was also present at the event.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body stalls action on illegal building work in MC Layout
news.para: Despite directions from the High Court to the Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP), the construction of buildings in violation of norms continues in the city.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body cuts water supply to five societies over defunct STPs
news.para: These five were among the 50 societies that had been served three notices in the last one year, a civic official said. "We also shared details about agencies that could help them repair such defunct plants, but they still did not comply with this mandatary provision."

news.title: Builder scraps commercial complex in Ghaziabad, told to repay buyer booking fee
news.para: Airwil Developers Private Limited, a private builder, had proposed a commercial complex, Airwil Wow, in Mohan Nagar and had collected advance payments from buyers for shops.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders Expressway Towers' builder to pay buyer 11% interest over project delay
news.para: The builder assured timely possession of the flat, with a carpet area of 644 sqft and a balcony area of 100 sqft, but failed to deliver within the stipulated four-year period from the date of allotment — May 19, 2017.

news.title: MHADA to provide ₹20,000 monthly rent for residents of 96 dangerous cessed buildings
news.para: Sanjeev Jaiswal, vice president and chief executive officer, MHADA, that tenants and residents of these buildings who independently arrange for alternate accommodation, will be provided monthly rent of ₹20,000 by the board.

news.title: Tesla secures fourth India office in Mumbai as part of expansion strategy
news.para: Tesla has leased a 24,500 sq ft office in Mumbai’s Kurla as part of its growing India presence, marking its fourth office in the country. The five-year lease, valued over ₹24 crore, follows Tesla’s recent showroom lease in BKC. These moves signal Tesla’s increasing operational focus and preparation for future manufacturing amid evolving EV policies in India.
